From 9474c12c33ca456fdbb10a21fdd2d9c0e7d9d02f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: iarantes <israel.arantesmoraes@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 14:50:59 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Fix OVS-DPDK alternative priority for Trixie

In Debian Trixie, the openvswitch-switch-dpdk package registers its
ovs-vswitchd binary with alternatives priority 50, while
openvswitch-switch registers with priority 100. This causes the
non-DPDK version to be selected by default, resulting in
"DPDK not supported in this copy of Open vSwitch" errors when
vswitchType is set to ovs-dpdk.

On Bullseye, the DPDK version had priority 200. Upstream Debian
lowered it to 50 for Trixie because DPDK requires SSE3 which not
all generic amd64 systems support. For StarlingX this is not a
concern as all supported hardware exceeds SSE3.

This patch restores the DPDK alternative priority to 200 so it
takes precedence when both packages are installed.

---
 debian/openvswitch-switch-dpdk.postinst | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/debian/openvswitch-switch-dpdk.postinst
+++ b/debian/openvswitch-switch-dpdk.postinst
@@ -5,7 +5,7 @@
 case "$1" in
     configure)
         update-alternatives --install /usr/sbin/ovs-vswitchd ovs-vswitchd \
-            /usr/lib/openvswitch-switch-dpdk/ovs-vswitchd-dpdk 50
+            /usr/lib/openvswitch-switch-dpdk/ovs-vswitchd-dpdk 200
         ;;
 
     abort-upgrade|abort-remove|abort-deconfigure)
